WS-Fed Passive Requestor Profile profile handler
August 20, 2013
Version 0.9
-------------------
This profile-handler implements an authentication handler for the
Shibboleth IdP and will set the authentication context class
"urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:ac:classes:wsfed".

License
  See LICENSE file

Source Access
  https://svn.shibboleth.net/extensions/TBC
  
Issue Tracking
  TBC

Comments & Questions
  adam_j_bradley@hotmail.com
  
  
  
----------------------------------------------------------------
Build and install:
-----------------------------------------------------------

Build:
1) copy jar to idp
   cp target/wsfed.jar $idpsrc/lib

3) copy webapp files to idp src
   cp resources/webapp/???.jsp $idpsrc/src/main/webapp

Configure:
1) handler.xml
   Add a namespace and a schema location.

      <ProfileHandlerGroup xmlns="urn:mace:shibboleth:2.0:idp:profile-handler"
           xmlns:uw="urn:mace:shibboleth:2.0:idp:uw"
           xmlns:icard="urn:mace:shibboleth:2.0:idp:infocard"
           xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
           xsi:schemaLocation="urn:mace:shibboleth:2.0:idp:profile-handler classpath:/schema/shibboleth-2.0-idp-profile-handler.xsd
           ProfileHandlerWSFedNamespaceHandler classpath:/edu/internet2/middleware/shibboleth/wsfed/wsfed.xsd ">
  
2) Add profile handler path definitions (e.g.)

<!-- WSFed handlers -->

    <ProfileHandler xsi:type="wsfed:Status">
        <RequestPath>/wsfed/status</RequestPath>
    </ProfileHandler>
    <ProfileHandler xsi:type="wsfed:PassiveRequstorProfile">
      <RequestPath>/wsfed/prp</RequestPath>
    </ProfileHandler>

